@startuml
!include ../../styles/plantuml-theme.puml
title Horizon Bank migration control thread
top to bottom direction
scale 750 width
skinparam nodesep 18
skinparam ranksep 22
skinparam defaultFontSize 13
rectangle "Trigger and intake\nOutcome, scope, evidence" as Intake #DDEBF7
rectangle "Impact and dependencies\nService, data, controls, owners" as Impact #DDEBF7
rectangle "Architecture states\nCurrent | transition | target" as States #E4DFEC
rectangle "Bounded migration wave\nEntry, exit, support, fallback" as Wave #E2F0D9
rectangle "Rehearsal and readiness\nData, operations, people, risk" as Ready #FFF2CC
hexagon "Proceed?" as Gate #FFF2CC
rectangle "Cutover\nTransfer bounded cohort" as Cutover #FCE4D6
rectangle "Verify and reconcile\nService, records, control totals" as Verify #E2F0D9
hexagon "Evidence acceptable?" as Check #FFF2CC
rectangle "Fallback to recoverable boundary\nRestore service, reconcile, reassess" as Fallback #F4CCCC
rectangle "Stabilise and decommission\nClose residual obligations" as Close #D9EAD3
rectangle "Benefits and feedback\nUpdate models, risks and next wave" as Learn #D9EAD3
Intake --> Impact : assess change
Impact --> States : establish baseline and direction
States --> Wave : define operable sequence
Wave --> Ready : prepare and rehearse
Ready --> Gate : submit readiness evidence
Gate --> Cutover : proceed authority
Gate --> Ready : stop and correct
Cutover --> Verify : migrate and observe
Verify --> Check : present evidence
Check --> Close : acceptable
Check --> Fallback : failed check
Fallback --> Impact : reassess assumptions
Close --> Learn : measure outcomes
Learn --> Impact : inform later wave
legend bottom
Every decision arrow is labelled. A failed check returns to a defined
recoverable boundary; the roadmap and target remain assumption-based.
endlegend
@enduml
